<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SLAYING-SUSPECT-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GRANDVIEW POLICE SEE NO LINK BETWEEN LIBERTY CASE, UNSOLVED
SLAYING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By OSCAR AVILA and SHAWNA A. HAMEL  
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Detectives returned from Texas on Thursday
with no evidence that William Brouse was linked to a killing in
Grandview, Mo., last year.
</P>
<P>
   Brouse, 25, died this week in a shootout with police in Plano,
Texas. Clay County, Mo., authorities had been seeking him in the
killing of Christy Schroeder near Liberty, Mo., in July.
</P>
<P>
   Grandview police were focusing on the killing Aug. 31 of Gary
Stein, who operated a sports memorabilia shop in Leawood, Kan., in
suburban Kansas City. They interviewed Cheryl Stein, his widow.
Stein now lives in Plano and had been in contact with Brouse in
recent weeks, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   But investigators were not able to connect Brouse with Stein's
death.
</P>
<P>
   ``Brouse was never a suspect,'' said Grandview Sgt. Kent Bruce.
``There's nothing to tie in to a homicide.
</P>
<P>
   ``We still have an ongoing investigation with Gary Stein. It's
an open case. We haven't got a thing on it.''
</P>
<P>
   Clay County authorities, meanwhile, explored the links among
Brouse, Cheryl Stein and Schroeder, whose body was found in a pond
near Liberty in what police think was a random killing.
</P>
<P>
   Clay County authorities planned to interview Stein.
</P>
<P>
   Lt. Steve Wright of the Sheriff's Department said interviews
with witnesses indicated that Brouse had been in contact with Stein
about the time Schroeder was killed. Authorities hope that Brouse's
phone records and the interview with Stein will confirm that.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities are not sure of the nature of their relationship but
suspect Brouse might have visited Stein in Texas. Clay County
authorities will continue their investigation to see whether anyone
might have aided Brouse while he eluded police.
</P>
<P>
   Just before Brouse was killed, Clay County prosecutors were
preparing to file an array of charges against him in Schroeder's
death, including murder, kidnapping, robbery and armed criminal
action.
</P>
<P>
   Surveillance videotapes and witness statements already placed
Brouse at the Schroeder crime scene, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities also hope to establish links between the weapons in
the Schroeder killing and the Plano shootout.
</P>
<P>
   Clay County investigators say a 9mm Beretta pistol was found at
the scene of the Plano shootout. Don Norris of the Clay County
prosecutor's office said authorities found a 9mm slug at the
Schroeder crime scene. And, Norris said, a 9mm weapon was stolen
from Gary Stein's home when he was killed.
</P>
<P>
   Plano police shot Brouse several times, but investigators also
discovered evidence of a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the head,
said Lynn Salzberger, the acting county medical examiner.
</P>
<P>
   Salzberger said her final report would not be finished for
several weeks. But, she said, investigators might not be able to
make a ruling on whether Brouse died from police gunfire or by his
own hand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
