   TAX-ASSESS _ A news analysis: Are the Republicans, or perhaps
the Democrats, driving off a political cliff on tax cuts? Almost
all Republicans in Congress favor one, and almost all Democrats are
against it. Rarely have both parties sounded equally confident
about the political benefits they think their policies, decided on
principle alone, of course, will bring. With each side sated with
polling data and focus group results, the conflict suggests that at
least one side is taking a big chance on the voters. By Adam
Clymer.
