<P>
   SALES-TAX-TEXAS (Houston) _ As Texas retailers gear up for the
state's first sales tax holiday, which started Friday and continues
through midnight Sunday, one big question remains to be answered.
Will shoppers embrace the event and stampede the stores like they
do on, say, the day after Thanksgiving or the day after Christmas?
Or will the dismiss it as a political gimmick that offers little
relief for their pocketbook ? By GREG HASSELL.
