SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ FAYETTE COUNTY, Ga. _ Discovering you're no
longer welcome in your own home is a sad experience. The best I can
say for my wife is that she tried to break the news diplomatically.
(Jim Minter is a former editor of The Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ There's a notion being hustled around naively _
or is it slyly? _ that we've become a colorblind nation and that
after 350 years of severe racial oppression and 30 of indifferent
relief, the books are squared and broad efforts at racial catch-up
such as affirmative action abuse the downtrodden white folk. The
problem with this scenario is that reality keeps rudely intruding.
(Tom Teepen is national correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED
THURSDAY FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ There seems to be no end to creative
lawsuits, giving support to consumer advocate Ralph Nader's
recurring contention that a museum be built to acclaim our wackiest
litigations. Just last week, two cases arose on either side of the
continent that could rival the case of the woman who spilled hot
coffee in her lap at McDonald's. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist
for Cox News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ PRAGUE _ Prague is a city intoxicated on
freedom, and that's not all. It's not unusual to meet someone along
the street smoking a joint. It takes some getting used to. But
then, so does the weather girl on TV, who appears totally nude and
then begins to dress herself accordingly for the next day's
weather. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED FRIDAY FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ Wall Street's wedded bliss with the
Internet now seems in need of a marriage counselor. When the market
capital of an online firm that sells discounted airline tickets
exceeds the combined stock value of several major airlines, there
well may be a reason to seek a divorce. (Andy Glass is a columnist
for Cox News Service in the Washington bureau.) MOVED THURSDAY FOR
SUNDAY.
</P>
