demonstrating one of its most remarkable aptitudes, that of
creative literary recycling. ``The Basics of Craftsmanship'' can
serve as a useful augmentation to the first volume of Tage Frid's
trilogy, ``Tage Frid Teaches Woodworking: Joinery _ Tools and
Techniques,'' but it won't replace it. I doubt anything ever will.
(Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED FOR SATURDAY
