could give soccer players a career-threatening injury. A study
carried out in London suggests that players are especially prone to
arthritic knee injuries triggered by sexually transmitted bacteria.
550 words. By Andy Coghlan. Slugged:
BC-SEX-BAD-FOR-KNEES-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
