might rid people of inflammatory bowel disease, such as Crohn's
disease, say researchers in Iowa. They believe this condition is on
the rise in the developing world due to the absence of intestinal
parasites. By Andy Coghlan. Slugged:
BC-WORMS-FOR-HEALTH-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
