<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sisters are doin' it for themselves at shopping expo
 &HT;    Jeffry Scott
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service'
<TEXT>
<P>
   For two days, there will be a shopping mall devoted to black
consumers in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   For Sisters Only: The Ultimate Family Experience runs today and
Sunday at the Georgia World Congress Center. More than 300 vendors
will sell merchandise from booths.
</P>
<P>
   The event is also a big-name concert series. Hosted by V-103 FM
and its sister station, WAOK-AM (1380), it features some of music's
hottest R&AMP;B bands.
</P>
<P>
   Acts that will appear over the two-day expo include: Destiny's
Child (4:30 p.m today), Trina Broussard (6:30 p.m. today), Faith
Evans (5 p.m. Sunday), Case (5:30 p.m. Sunday) and Dru Hill (7 p.m.
Sunday).
</P>
<P>
   Last year the event drew 60,000. This year, in a bigger hall, it
may draw more, predicted Rick Caffey, vice president and general
manager of V-103.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can see a whole day's worth of top-notch acts for $10 and
go shopping, too,'' Caffey said. ``It's the largest consumer expo
targeted toward the African-American family in the country.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition, there will be autograph-signing sessions with
actors Taurean Blacque (3-4 p.m. today), Whitman Mayo (2:30-3:30
p.m. Sunday) and musicians Usher (6-7 p.m. today), Tracey Edmonds
(1-2 p.m. Sunday) and Ginuwine (3-4 p.m. Sunday).
</P>
<P>
   Other events and exhibits include:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  An exhibit celebrating the 45-year history of WAOK and its
impact on the city.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A storytelling session with former WXIA newscaster Steen
Miles, from 4 to 6 p.m. today and 5:30-7 p.m. Sunday in the
Cultural Pavilion.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Exhibits from the Ballethnic Dance Company, the Morgan County
African American Museum, the Fernbank Museum of Natural History and
the High Museum of Art.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A church service led by the Rev. Dreyfus Smith and the Wings
of Faith Ministries and Family Life Center of East Point, at 10
a.m. Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Georgia World
</P>
<P>
   Congress Center
</P>
<P>
   When: 10 a.m.- 8 p.m. today and Sunday
</P>
<P>
   Admission: $10. Children under 6 free. (Free admission 10
a.m.-11 a.m. Sunday.)
</P>
<P>
   Information: Call 404-898-8900, Ext. 8811, or on the Web at
www.v-103.com
</P>
<P>
   Jeffry Scott writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
