are gone. After hanging on through the booms and busts of a fickle
cowboy boot market, through two layoffs of 40 employees each, and
years of downsizing through attrition, the surviving boot makers of
Nocona are smiling through their tears. But their eyes are moister
than their grins are large. By BARRY SHLACHTER. Story will move in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
