<P>
   ARMY-WIFE-DRUGS (New York) _ The wife of an Army colonel
involved in U.S. counternarcotics operations in Colombia is facing
federal charges of shipping large amounts of cocaine to the United
States earlier this year. The woman, Laurie Hiett, is the wife of
Army Col. James Hiett, who at the time was in charge of all U.S.
military activities in Colombia, including counterdrug operations.
By Robert D. McFadden.
