<HEADLINE>
TALK MAGAZINE GOES BACK ON PRESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Hearst Magazines announced Friday that Talk magazine
will print an additional 300,000 copies of its inaugural issue to
meet unexpected demand.
</P>
<P>
   Launched Aug. 3 with an initial press run of 1,000,000 copies,
Talk is the fastest selling title in Hearst history, according to
Cathleen P. Black, president of Hearst Magazines.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is an unbelievable response to the debut issue of Talk,''
Black said.
</P>
<P>
   Hearst Magazines is a unit of The Hearst Corporation.
</P>
