   BLUE-ANGELS (Seattle) _ In the anonymous world of the Blue
Angels pilots, they call him No. 2, the right wing, who flies 36
inches off his boss's wingtip at speeds where a tiny mistake could
spell disaster. As the Angels' F/A-18 Hornet fighter jets scream
across Lake Washington this weekend, few spectators will know that
No. 2 is a pinch hitter.
</P>
