   TRIDENT (ABOARD THE USS FLORIDA) _ The Florida, a Trident
missile submarine and three other submarines at Bangor on
Washington's Hood Canal may soon by trading in their
nuclear-warhead missiles and taking on a new mission. Instead of
being retired from lurking deep in the Pacific for the contingency
of nuclear war, the oldest four Bangor submarines could be
converted into cruise-missile ships that would be sent to crisis
areas such as the Persian Gulf, Korea or the Balkans.
