<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Friday, 08/06/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT40) LAKE WARAMAUG STATE PARK, Conn. -- Aug. 06, 1999 --
DROUGHT-MOSQUITOS-2, 08-06 -- As dusk descends on campsite No. 35
at Lake Waramaug, the Grom family is deep in mosquito-free
enjoyment, gathering around the flickering fire; the mosquito net
attached to their trailer was left open all day. Thanks to the
drought, mosquitoes are as scarce as the little puddles and pools
their eggs need to hatch. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT39) JERUSALEM -- Aug. 06, 1999 -- ISRAEL-VIOLENCE-2, 08-06
-- Youths crowding a sidewalk in Jerusalem. More than before, some
say, violence has broken out in such circumstances, as happened
Friday. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT38) NAGASAKI, Japan. -- Aug. 06, 1999 -- ATOM-COX-2-B&AMP;W,
08-05 -- The destruction rendered by the dropping of the atomic
bomb on Nagasaki. ``I'd never heard the phrase, 'atomic bomb,' ``
says Motor Machinist's Mate 3rd Class J. Norman Ingram, who took
the photo, recalling how he learned about the devastation of
Hiroshima on Aug. 6, 1945. ``But it sounded like it was just what
we needed.'' (J. Norman Ingram/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT37) NAGASAKI, Japan -- Aug. 06, 1999 -- ATOM06-COX-1-B&AMP;W,
08-05 -- Family photo of Motor Machinist's Mate 3rd Class J. Norman
Ingram, right, following the atomic bomb blast in Nagasaki. ``We
didn't know what to expect,'' he says. Although Japan had
surrendered, no treaty had been signed. ``To be honest, I was
frightened. We wondered if they'd let the fleet sail in and then
try to trap us.'' (Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) UNDATED -- Aug. 06, 1999 -- SHOPPING-GUIDE-COX, 08-04 --
